<gco:CharacterString>These raster data of the top surface of the Paleozoic formation of the Upper Colorado River Basin (UCRB) were created for the purpose of developing a generalized predevelopment groundwater flow model of the Mesozoic and Paleozoic aquifers in the Upper Colorado River Basin and use that model along with a few recharge estimates to estimate water budgets for the aquifers including associated groundwater contributions to the Colorado River surface water system. The modeling exercise also explored considerations for development of a more detailed groundwater flow model that would include all of the major aquifers in the Upper Colorado River Basin.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>These data were derived from various other sources (maps) in order to present a cohesive top of the Paleozoic rocks in the Upper Colorado River Basin for use in the development of the Upper Colorado River Basin Groundwater Flow Model.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:purpose> Depth contours from PP1411-A, Plate 3 (2003), altitude contours of the top of Permian rocks in the San Juan Basin area from Bulletin 1808-O Figure 18 (1993), and from NARGFM top of model layer 1 (top of Kaibab land surface). The land-surface digital elevation models(DEM) used to derive depths were developed as follows: Land surface in the study area includes DEM in the area of the UCRB and adjacent areas outside of the UCRB in New Mexico and Arizona. The areas outside of UCRB were included to account for areas of recharge to Mesozoic and Paleozoic rocks that contribute to UCRB GW budgets and areas of discharge from Paleozoic and Mesozoic rocks to the Colorado and Little Colorado rivers. 1. The UCRB DEM is a 100m grid file \ufffd\ufffd€œdem_nad83_utm\ufffd\ufffd€ 2. The source of New Mexico DEM is the NW and SW state quadrant DEMs at 30m resolution. \ufffd\ufffd€œnm_ned09_30m_nw_qtr2\ufffd\ufffd€ and \ufffd\ufffd€œnm_ned09_30m_sw_qtr2\ufffd\ufffd€ 3. The source of northern Arizona DEMs is a 500m DEM derived from 10m DEMs for the NARGFM study area. 4. DEMs were merged using the UCRB DEM as the dominant raster to produce \ufffd\ufffd€œUCRpaleo_LSA\ufffd\ufffd€ for the entire study area including extents of Paleozoic rock that may contribute to UCRB GW flow in AZ and NM. For stream elevation use the DEMs were processed to determine the minimum elevation within each 500-meter cell. \ufffd\ufffd€œucrb_500m_minlsa.tif\ufffd\ufffd€</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:supplementalInformation>       </gmd:MD_DataIdentification>    </gmd:identificationInfo>    <gmd:contentInfo><!-- translated from eainfo/detailed to MD_CoverageDescription--><gmd:MD_CoverageDescription>          <gmd:attributeDescription gco:nilReason="unknown"/>          <gmd:contentType gco:nilReason="unknown"/>          <!--FGDC content not mapped to ISO.
